        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"176352\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"176352\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"176352\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>As per Allen Meadow\u2019s in 2002: \u201cIt is with great sadness that I report that M. Amiot has elected to sell his vines and as such, 1999 is the final vintage. The Amiot family faced what is becoming more common these days in Burgundy and that is the lack of a successor. M. Amiot had offspring capable of assuming his role but not the interest and thus the decision was made to sell.\u201d</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yeah not sure who got his vines</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think it was Jadot but I may be misremembering. This question was asked last year.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think he had charmes and chatelots for 1er</p>",
